'''noseflute'''
{{cleanup}}
# A [[handheld]] [[musical]] [[instrument]], usually made from hard [[plastic]].  Despite the name, it does not actually look like a flute.  It has a hole near the bottom, which is held in front of the mouth, and the entrance to the hollow at the top is put under and in front of the nostrils.  To play it, you blow out of your nose and move your lips into different shapes, which determines the pitch.  The noseflute's musical range is roughly an octave, but some skilled players can reach an octave and a half.  Generally, it can be learned very quickly and with no instruction, despite the weirdness of making music by blowing out of your nose.